"When the Tor Browser starts, the Oz sandbox limits its access to files and "
"directories on the computer. For example, a photo from the `Pictures` "
"directory will not be visible in the sandbox by default. If you want to "
"upload a photo from this directory, you must use the Oz menu to add it to "
"the Tor Browser sandbox. The Oz menu is denoted by the little zebra icon at "
"the top-right corner of the screen."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 04_everyday-usage_02_torbrowser.md:86 04_everyday-usage_02_torbrowser.md:86
msgid ""
"> ![Oz menu - icon](static/images/oz_menu_zebra.png){#id .class width=60 "
"height=60px} > The following actions may be performed using the Oz menu: > > "
"- Add files to sandbox > > - Open terminal in sandbox > > - Shutdown sandbox"
