#. type: Plain text
#: 05_features_and_advanced_usage_05_macouflage.md:2
msgid "## Anonymizing MAC addresses with Macouflage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 05_features_and_advanced_usage_05_macouflage.md:6
msgid ""
"MAC addresses are the unique identifiers for the network interface on the "
"computer (such as Ethernet ports and WIFI cards). Due to their unique "
"nature, they can also compromise the privacy of the user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 05_features_and_advanced_usage_05_macouflage.md:13
msgid ""
"When connecting to a network, it is possible for other devices on the "
"network to see the MAC address of the network interface that is "
"connected. While this is not much of a concern on networks you trust such as "
"your home network, it may compromise your privacy on those who do not "
"trust. On untrustworthy or hostile networks, uniquely identifying "
"characteristics such as the MAC address may allow others to track your "
"computer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 05_features_and_advanced_usage_05_macouflage.md:19
msgid ""
"Subgraph OS mitigates this privacy risk by always creating random MAC "
"addresses for all of your network interfaces. Each time one of your "
"interfaces connects to a network, it will use a different MAC address. This "
"helps to anonymize you across different networks or when connecting to the "
"same network over and over again."
msgstr ""

